OL,6,FIdentifying as Christian in England and
OL,7,FWales has fallen to a record low,
OL,8,Faccording to the latest results from
OL,9,Fthe 2021 census.
OL,11,FThe proportion of the population
OL,12,Fdescribing themselves as Christian
OL,13,Fdropped below half for the first time,
OL,14,Fthe Office for National Statistics
OL,15,F(ONS) said.
OL,17,FAt the time of the last census 10 years
OL,18,Fago, 59.3 per cent of people described
OL,19,Fthemselves as Christian, but now the
OL,20,Ffigure is 46.2 per cent.
OL,3,CChristianity in England and Wales falls
OL,4,Cbelow 50% for the first time, says ONS
